Functions - standalone procedures that perform a specific task\
def add_numbers(a, b):
    return a + b

Methods - functions that are associated with an object
class MyClass:
    def my_method(self):
        print("This is a method of MyClass.")

Attributes - associated with an object and are used to store data related to the object
class MyClass:
    def __init__(self, my_attribute):
        self.my_attribute = my_attribute